movies.title: Inside
movies.plot: Alex has a disturbing hobby of following strangers...until one night he gets caught. Instead of calling the police, the couple--fascinated by Alex's resemblance to their dead son--asks him to stay, and Alex finds himself trapped in a horrifying existence of desperation, despair, and insanity.
movies.simplePlot: A man's interest in a couple leads to chilling and heartbreaking results.

biography.bio: Nicholas D'Agosto was born and raised in Omaha, Nebraska. He is the son of Deanna Rae (Vellinga) and Alan D'Agosto, who franchises Arby's restaurants. His ancestry includes Italian (from his father) and Dutch (his maternal grandfather). Nicholas was a student when he was cast in Election (1999), which filmed in Omaha. He later moved to Milwaukee, Wisconsin to attend school at Marquette University, graduating cum laude with degrees in History and Theatre. The middle of five children (two older brothers, two younger sisters), Nicholas has only seen his family expand as he has become an uncle.
biography.name: Nicholas D'Agosto

biography.bio: Cheryl White is an actress, known for Major Crimes (2012), The Book of Daniel (2006) and Nip/Tuck (2003).
biography.name: Cheryl White

biography.bio: Kevin Kilner was born on May 3, 1958 in Baltimore, Maryland, USA. He is an actor, known for Home Alone 3 (1997), A Cinderella Story (2004) and American Pie 2 (2001). He has been married to Jordan Baker since 1998.
biography.name: Kevin Kilner

biography.bio: Leighton Marissa Meester was born in Fort Worth, Texas, to Constance (Haas) and Douglas Meester. Although born in Texas when her mother was serving a jail sentence for her part in a marijuana-smuggling ring, Meester spent her early years in Marco Island, Florida with her grandparents. There, she became involved with the local playhouse and made her stage debut in a production of "The Wizard of Oz". She moved to New York with her mother at the age of 11 and was soon working as a model and appearing in TV commercials. A few years later, at age 14, she and her mother moved again, this time to Los Angeles where she soon began to pick up TV work, making her debut in Law & Order: Disciple (1999). A steady stream of TV work followed until in 2007 she landed the role in Gossip Girl (2007) which made her famous. This led to more TV and movie work, and in 2009 she launched a recording career with a single entitled, "Somebody to Love".
biography.name: Leighton Meester

biography.bio: Barbara Allyne Bennet was born in 1940 in Cleveland, Ohio, USA. She is known for her work on Mac and Me (1988), Raid on Entebbe (1976) and Evita Peron (1981). She died on January 9, 2016 in Duarte, California, USA.
biography.name: Barbara Allyne Bennet

biography.bio: Corey Bodoh-Creed was born in Washington, District of Columbia, USA. He is a director and producer, known for Bad High (2008), I Miss My Gun (2012) and Gil's Brother (2011).
biography.name: Corey Bodoh-Creed

biography.bio: Robert Clotworthy was born on October 24, 1955 in Los Angeles, California, USA as Robert Bruce Clotworthy. He is known for his work on American Sniper (2014), Ancient Aliens (2009) and The Curse of Oak Island (2014).
biography.name: Robert Clotworthy

biography.name: Candice Hamilton

biography.bio: Rob was raised in Eugene, Oregon... then in DeKalb, Illinois... and then in Williamsburg, Virginia... he is a self-professed "faculty brat." He graduated from Northwestern University in 1992 with a double-major in theatre and philosophy. Rob spent a season at the Shakespeare Theatre in Washington, DC, performing in productions of Macbeth, Henry V, All's Well that Ends Well, Volpone, and Measure for Measure. He is a member of the Antaeus Company and the Troubadour Theater Company.
biography.name: Rob Nagle

biography.bio: Mark Riley was born on November 30, 1977 in Woodville, Florida, USA as Mark Riley Wilkinson. He is an actor and producer, known for Deadtectives (2017), Rally (2015) and Dartsville (2007).
biography.name: Mark Riley

biography.bio: Larry Sullivan was born on September 10, 1970 in New Haven, Connecticut, USA as Lawrence Edward Sullivan Jr. He is an actor, known for Rush Hour (1998), Straight Outta Compton (2015) and Fracture (2007).
biography.name: Larry Sullivan

biography.bio: Ursula was born and raised in Los Angeles, California. She is a graduate of the University of Southern California with a BA in American Literature and a minor in Film/TV. She wrote and performed stand-up comedy for several years. Her work as a monologist has been published in "The Los Angeles Times Magazine". With a background in dance, acting, and writing, Ursula makes her directorial debut with the comedic short film "Boob Jobs & Jesus". She adapted the short film from her feature length script which, in turn, was adapted from her one act play. Ursula gained a considerable portion of her theatre acting experience as a member of Theatre Neo in Los Angeles. She performed in such plays as "Your Mother's Butt" by Alan Ball, "Big Mistake" by Theresa Rebeck, "Coming Attractions" by Ted Tally and Ursula's own one act play, "Boob Jobs & Jesus". She went on to perform in Thomas Babe's "Taken in Marriage" directed by Emmy Award-Winning Actress Dorothy Lyman.
biography.name: Ursula Whittaker
